==English== 
===Etymology===
Possessive of [[you]] + [[all]] + [[-'s]], formed after [[you all]].

===Pronoun=== 
'''your all’s'''
# ''(colloquial)'' Belonging to the multiple persons being addressed.

===Quotations=== 
* '''1982,''' United States Senate Committee on Finance, ''Tuition Tax Credit Proposals'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&vid=OCLC09290207&id=p88KC1hVqHcC&q=%22your+all%27s%22&dq=%22your+all%27s%22&pgis=1]
*: And yet, '''your all’s''' close questioning goes right to the heart of the discrimination and everything else, and that’s the basis of their operation.
* '''1998,''' [[w:Barbara Kingsolver|Barbara Kingsolver]], ''The Bean Trees'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&vid=ISBN0061097314&id=O-XiVJO1K1gC&pg=PA253&lpg=PA253&dq=%22your+all%27s%22&sig=5Da_gaMm3H8qL9XdRqNEJb2XkMg]
*: “Bless '''your all’s''' hearts,” she said. “Take good care.”
* '''2004,''' [[w:George Pelecanos|George Pelecanos]], ''Soul Circus'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&vid=ISBN0446611425&id=RCjLCwr8XikC&pg=PA20&lpg=PA20&dq=%22your+all%27s%22&sig=cqBMtWCUeBgQTgUcwVxmTXWiDbM]
